    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-06-08T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-06-08T11:00:00-05:00" n="296"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d296">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">862.5151/1882: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-08T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >June 8, 1938—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 8—1 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>295. Foreign exchange circular order dated June 4 and published last night
                    provides in effect that permission will no longer be granted to Jews to sell
                    emigrants’ blocked marks against payment in foreign exchange. Exception,
                    however, is made for foreign Jews and Jews whose total property is less than
                    5000 marks. The order goes into effect immediately.</p>
                <pb facs="0384" n="376" xml:id="pg_376"/>
                <p>With the exceptions noted, this order will have the effect of preventing Jews
                    from receiving upon emigration from Germany even the greatly reduced amounts
                    formerly available to them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
